        "timestamp": "2017-10-03 15:08:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review\n\n> > That doesn't seems to have done the trick\n > \n > Hmm... I'll give it a shot for you then.\n\nOk, so the correct method to fix that was:\n\ngit checkout master\ngit pull\ngit submodule update --init\ngit check $localbranch\ngit rebase master\ngit commit -as --amend\n\nThe 'git submodule update --init' needed to happen while on the master branch, not while on your branch.",
